text: section 19.7 of the pro forma oatt only obligates the tp to tell the customer how much partial long term service could be provided.
label: None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None

text: examples: -- customer requests 300 mw long term transmission service for one year.  tp replies that it can offer 200 mw for the entire year. -- customer requests 2 year service for 300 mw.  tp replies that it can offer 300 mw for one year. -- customer requests 300 mw for one year.  tp can only provide 300 mw for summer months.  tp is not obligated to provide customer the 3 months service.

text: here is a summary of the comments.
label: None None None None None None None

text: marketing affiliate concerns.
label: None None None

text: bp's regulatory representative expressed concern that tw's marketing affiliates would be able to use options to game the system.
label: None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None

text: in bp's example, since tw and ena are both enron companies, ena could purchase an ""out of the money"" call option essentially cost free, since its affiliate (tw) would have the ability to buy the option back.
label: None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None

text: proceeds from ena's ability to then ""move the market"" through the establishment of the long basis position would go directly to enron's bottom line.
label: None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None

text: bp suggested that tw's marketing affiliates be banned from purchasing options, or that the marketing affiliate be required to credit 100% of the option proceeds to other shippers.
label: None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None

text: although bp admits that transwestern's prior dealings with ena have not been suspect, bp fears that tw's filing will set a precedent for other pipelines to offer a similar service.
label: None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None

text: since tw will be the first pipeline to offer such services, bp wants tw's program to be as restricted as possible.
label: None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None

text: dynegy echoed bp's concern regarding possible affiliate abuse, but rather than shelve the program entirely, dynegy reiterated an earlier suggestion that transwestern be required to credit back the difference between the option fee paid by an affiliate and the next highest bidder, if the affiliate's bid exceeds the next highest by a certain percentage.
label: None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None

text: tw's response was that while actual abuse of an options program by a marketing affiliate may be a legitimate concern, owing to its unassailable record in this area, tw should be entitled to a presumption that it has complied and will continue to comply with commission policy covering the sale of capacity to marketing affiliates, and was not inclined to voluntarily include any limitations on the options program.
label: None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None

text: if bp and others have serious concerns regarding the commission's overall policy on marketing affiliates, those issues should be raised in a separate proceeding that applies to all interstate pipelines.
label: None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None None
